******
[1] Blast - Bhutan (Sarpang)
Date: Sat 28 Oct 2017
Source: Kuensel [edited]
http://www.kuenselonline.com/rice-blast-affects-chudzom-farmers/


With rice blast affecting at least 25 per cent of paddy in [parts of] Sarpang [district,], [a] farmer said, "We're seeing such rice disease for the 1st time here." Farmers fear the disease will wipe out entire fields. "It is spreading rapidly, it began 2 weeks ago."

Farmers are worried about seeds for the next cultivation. "I'm hopeful that I would be able to sort out uninfected rice for seeds," [a farmer] said. "Otherwise we may have to buy new seeds."

Agriculture officials said the immediate measure taken to avoid further damage of crop was to advice farmers for immediate harvest.

[Byline: Nirmala Pokhrel]

